1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:05,505
<i>What other sins do you think</i>
<i>I could have committed against you?</i>

2
00:00:05,588 --> 00:00:07,757
<i>Did you seriously think</i>
<i>I didn't catch you two?</i>

3
00:00:07,841 --> 00:00:09,509
<i>That I don't know</i>
<i>what happened between you?</i>

4
00:00:09,592 --> 00:00:11,594
- [WENDY] <i>That's not true--</i>
- [GRETA]<i> Liar!</i>

5
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:12,929
<i>Traitor!</i>

6
00:00:13,012 --> 00:00:15,390
- [GRETA GRUNTS]
- [MAGNUS]<i> Greta! Greta! That's enough!</i>

7
00:00:16,057 --> 00:00:20,729
<i>You didn't hesitate</i>
<i>to take the blame for Ma'am Greta</i>

8
00:00:20,812 --> 00:00:22,981
<i>because you were feeling guilty.</i>

9
00:00:23,064 --> 00:00:24,733
<i>For my son.</i>

10
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:27,360
<i>For one night of weakness.</i>

11
00:00:27,444 --> 00:00:30,155
<i>Greta, I'm sorry for what happened</i>
<i>between me and Wendy.</i>

12
00:00:30,238 --> 00:00:32,323
<i>Can we please just leave that in the past?</i>

13
00:00:32,407 --> 00:00:36,661
<i>What matters now</i>
<i>is that we survive this as a family.</i>

14
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:39,456
<i>We need each other.</i>

15
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:43,126
<i>Olsen? I owe you.</i>

16
00:00:44,544 --> 00:00:45,712
<i>You have no fever.</i>

17
00:00:45,795 --> 00:00:47,297
<i>You're gonna survive.</i>

18
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:52,093
[ICE] <i>This is the first time</i>
<i>I've seen Liam up close.</i>

19
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:53,219
<i>He's pretty cute.</i>

20
00:00:53,303 --> 00:00:54,971
<i>I think I have a crush on him.</i>

21
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:57,515
<i>- Don't you have a boyfriend?</i>
<i>- It's just a crush.</i>

22
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:02,187
<i>Just kill me already.</i>

23
00:01:02,270 --> 00:01:03,396
<i>I don't care anymore.</i>

24
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:05,940
<i>So many people have died.</i>

25
00:01:06,024 --> 00:01:10,570
<i>We agreed we'd only ask for money.</i>
<i>I didn't know this would happen.</i>

26
00:01:10,653 --> 00:01:14,199
[MARISTELLA] <i>You had a hand</i>
<i>in what's happening at La Playa Roja.</i>

27
00:01:14,282 --> 00:01:18,620
<i>Please believe me, sir.</i>
<i>I really just want to do my job right.</i>

28
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:22,082
<i>The welfare of the hostages</i>
<i>is my priority.</i>

29
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:26,711
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

30
00:01:30,965 --> 00:01:37,931
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

31
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:41,100
[DOMINGO CHUCKLES]

32
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:44,979
You're pretty impressive, Jacinto.

33
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:47,440
I mean,

34
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:51,569
you even got Senator Maristella
to believe you.

35
00:01:52,862 --> 00:01:55,281
One lick of the higher-ups' shoes…

36
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:57,617
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,327
…and now you're free.

38
00:01:59,410 --> 00:02:01,246
You're always jumping to conclusions, sir.

39
00:02:02,205 --> 00:02:06,084
That's not what
a good police officer does, Major.

40
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:09,587
We don't act on mere suspicions.

41
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:10,672
[DOMINGO SCOFFS]

42
00:02:11,881 --> 00:02:14,634
If you're really innocent,

43
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:17,011
then prove it.

44
00:02:18,388 --> 00:02:23,810
Help save the hostages at La Playa Roja.

45
00:02:25,645 --> 00:02:27,814
I would have been doing already

46
00:02:28,523 --> 00:02:32,026
if you hadn't interfered, sir.

47
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:38,074
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

48
00:02:38,158 --> 00:02:41,703
I'll be watching your every move, Jacinto.

49
00:02:45,248 --> 00:02:47,500
One wrong move,

50
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:50,503
and I'll throw you back in jail.

51
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:53,339
And this time,

52
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:59,220
I'll make sure no one can get you out.

53
00:03:00,513 --> 00:03:07,312
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

54
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:22,911
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:55,068
I don't want to be
the cause of delay, Lieutenant.

56
00:03:55,151 --> 00:03:58,529
I'm ready to go as soon as we can leave.

57
00:03:59,113 --> 00:04:00,406
Okay.

58
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:03,034
But we're still waiting
for Cariaso's go signal

59
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:05,119
about whether our route is safe.

60
00:04:05,203 --> 00:04:07,497
Even if he says it's safe,

61
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,541
we both know that's no guarantee

62
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:13,878
we won't run into trouble.

63
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:15,922
So, Lieutenant,

64
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:18,424
I need a gun.

65
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:24,597
[BEN] Sir, you can trust him.

66
00:04:25,306 --> 00:04:28,226
If he and my grandson Olsen team up,

67
00:04:28,726 --> 00:04:30,436
we'll have the upper hand.

68
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,855
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:35,858
I'm happy you and Olsen have made up.

70
00:04:40,822 --> 00:04:42,865
He helped save my life.

71
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:47,453
I'll always be grateful
for that, Chief Ben.

72
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:51,624
And what matters most right now

73
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:56,087
is that we work together
for everyone's sake.

74
00:04:58,339 --> 00:05:04,262
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,888
[GUN CLINKING]

76
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:11,144
[AREZA] You're a chef.

77
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,813
How did you learn how to use a gun?

78
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:17,942
[LIAM] As well as martial arts,

79
00:05:18,026 --> 00:05:21,070
Chief Ben also taught me how to use a gun.

80
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,198
He's like a father to me.

81
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:30,663
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

82
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:33,624
[MAGNUS] <i>What matters now</i>

83
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:36,461
<i>is that we survive this as a family.</i>

84
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,756
[IAN] <i>I can't take it anymore.</i>

85
00:05:40,548 --> 00:05:42,592
<i>So many people have died.</i>

86
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:48,681
<i>We agreed we'd only ask for money.</i>
<i>I didn't know this would happen.</i>

87
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:54,145
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:05:54,228 --> 00:06:00,902
[UNSETTLING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

89
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:12,413
Congratulations, Chief.

90
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:14,248
You outsmarted Domingo.

91
00:06:14,832 --> 00:06:17,335
Luckily, Senator Maristella believed me.

92
00:06:18,461 --> 00:06:20,171
What's going on with our plan?

93
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:23,800
<i>Relax. We'll take care of it.</i>

94
00:06:24,675 --> 00:06:26,177
<i>Including Domingo.</i>

95
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:29,555
Is he still a problem?

96
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:34,185
Do you want a permanent solution?

97
00:06:34,268 --> 00:06:35,561
No need.

98
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:40,191
Just make sure there are no more problems.

99
00:06:40,274 --> 00:06:41,442
Mm.

100
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:55,123
[MAN ON RADIO]
<i>Menor, come in. Over.</i>

101
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,876
Any news on my brother?

102
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,211
Have you found him?

103
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:03,089
We've scoured the whole resort.

104
00:07:03,172 --> 00:07:04,215
Negative.

105
00:07:05,216 --> 00:07:08,469
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

106
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:09,637
Let's go!

107
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:23,109
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:40,543
[CARIASO] Alpha One, come in.

109
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:44,464
Alpha One, come in.

110
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:47,383
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

111
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:50,178
Alpha One, come in.

112
00:07:50,261 --> 00:07:51,971
The speedboats are still here.

113
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,348
The route here is still safe.

114
00:07:54,432 --> 00:07:55,558
Over.

115
00:07:56,976 --> 00:07:58,686
[WALKIE-TALKIE BEEPS]

116
00:07:58,769 --> 00:08:00,771
Come on, let's go back.

117
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:07,862
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:08:21,876 --> 00:08:26,005
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:08:27,298 --> 00:08:28,758
[MUSIC FADES]

120
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:31,886
Senator Maristella,

121
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:38,392
you're mistaken if you think
Jacinto can be trusted.

122
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:40,228
You even called the Chief of Police

123
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:43,105
just to have the investigation
on him stopped.

124
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:46,400
And who should I trust?

125
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,401
You?

126
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:50,780
Who allegedly has connections
to drug lords?

127
00:08:50,863 --> 00:08:53,783
Those accusations are baseless.

128
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:58,204
And your accusations against him
have any basis?

129
00:08:58,287 --> 00:09:02,333
Because it seems to me that
the money found on him was planted.

130
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:03,501
Look.

131
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:08,381
I don't care about the mudslinging
between the two of you.

132
00:09:08,464 --> 00:09:10,174
I just need my son back.

133
00:09:10,258 --> 00:09:12,843
And you will get your son back.

134
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:15,721
My men will protect him.

135
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:18,140
I give you my word.

136
00:09:18,891 --> 00:09:21,060
Well, your word is not good enough.

137
00:09:21,852 --> 00:09:24,647
Because we're talking about my son here!

138
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:29,318
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

139
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:30,903
[MUSIC FADES]

140
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:33,573
[LINE RINGING]

141
00:09:35,032 --> 00:09:36,534
[JERICHO] <i>Hello?</i>

142
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:38,744
Hello? Hello, Jericho?

143
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:39,996
Greta.

144
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:41,622
[GRETA] <i>What's going on?</i>

145
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:43,124
We had a deal, remember?

146
00:09:43,207 --> 00:09:47,712
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

147
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:48,879
Hello?

148
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:50,715
Jericho?

149
00:09:57,888 --> 00:09:59,056
You owe me.

150
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:03,227
You can count on me, Senator.

151
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:06,856
[UNSETTLING MUSIC SWELLS]

152
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:08,316
[LIAM] Ma?

153
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:09,817
Who are you talking to?

154
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:13,070
Who's Jericho?

155
00:10:13,863 --> 00:10:17,116
[STUTTERS] He's my contact
at the police station.

156
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:18,242
Uh…

157
00:10:18,326 --> 00:10:20,036
Nothing's still happened here.

158
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:22,121
We can't get out.

159
00:10:22,204 --> 00:10:24,373
Is any help still coming here?

160
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:25,625
Ma.

161
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:27,918
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:30,296
[LIAM] The police are doing
everything they can.

163
00:10:30,379 --> 00:10:32,465
We just have to let them do their jobs.

164
00:10:33,758 --> 00:10:35,468
Your son's right, Mrs. Roja.

165
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:37,762
We're doing everything we can.

166
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:42,767
In fact, we're just waiting for a signal
before we get you all out of here.

167
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:45,645
The main station will also
send more backup.

168
00:10:45,728 --> 00:10:50,358
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,942
Ma.

170
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:53,527
Keep calm.

171
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:04,955
Give us an update.

172
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:07,249
What happened to the rescue operation?

173
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:10,836
Is there a way for us
to contact our family there?

174
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:14,965
Your families are now in the care of
the police officers on the island.

175
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:19,678
We've also deployed additional
rescue units to evacuate them.

176
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:23,516
So what do you mean?
We will just sit here and wait?

177
00:11:23,599 --> 00:11:26,185
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

178
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:28,354
Senator, please help us!

179
00:11:28,437 --> 00:11:31,065
Our families haven't been rescued yet!

180
00:11:31,148 --> 00:11:33,150
As you know,

181
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:35,403
my son is also on the island.

182
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,988
But we have to trust our police.

183
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:43,160
I'm sure Captain Jacinto and his team
are keeping our families safe.

184
00:11:43,869 --> 00:11:47,832
But, Senator, please help us.
I'm begging you.

185
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:50,668
- I beg of you.
- Please, Mr. Senator.

186
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:52,253
You are our only chance.

187
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:57,925
- [PHONE RINGS]
- [FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYS]

188
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:02,179
Wait a second. Please excuse me.

189
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:07,393
[SCOFFS, SOBS]

190
00:12:07,476 --> 00:12:08,978
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

191
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:12,231
Please do not worry.
We're doing everything we can

192
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:14,650
to rescue everyone on that island.

193
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:21,282
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

194
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:49,477
[LUCAS] Mister Senator.

195
00:12:53,147 --> 00:12:55,733
You're quite obedient, Senator.

196
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:58,360
I won't count your payment.

197
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:00,905
But be sure that it's the right amount.

198
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:04,033
[EDUARDO] It's all there.

199
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:05,910
One hundred million!

200
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:09,413
[LUCAS] You really surprise me, Senator.

201
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:12,541
You deliver cash so quickly!

202
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:14,335
Where's my son?

203
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:19,215
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

204
00:13:19,298 --> 00:13:21,634
Son! How are you?

205
00:13:22,259 --> 00:13:23,427
Dad, I'm sorry.

206
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:27,097
I'm sorry for all my mistakes.

207
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:28,849
That's not important.

208
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:31,393
What matters is you're safe.

209
00:13:32,269 --> 00:13:33,938
I've done nothing

210
00:13:35,397 --> 00:13:37,483
but cause you trouble.

211
00:13:37,566 --> 00:13:39,568
[MUSIC TURNS MOROSE]

212
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:41,862
I've only embarrassed you.

213
00:13:43,405 --> 00:13:45,574
Embarrassed the family.

214
00:13:46,408 --> 00:13:48,494
<i>I keep promising I'll change, but</i>

215
00:13:49,411 --> 00:13:51,914
I keep breaking my promises.

216
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:56,544
I'm sorry.

217
00:13:56,627 --> 00:13:58,462
Listen to me, son.

218
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:02,675
What's important is you're safe,

219
00:14:02,758 --> 00:14:04,510
and you'll be home soon.

220
00:14:04,593 --> 00:14:06,470
Yes, Dad.

221
00:14:06,554 --> 00:14:12,434
[MUSIC TURNS SUSPENSEFUL]

222
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:17,398
You've been talking with my father.

223
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:19,942
Has he paid already?

224
00:14:20,901 --> 00:14:22,152
Tell me!

225
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:24,363
What else do you want?!

226
00:14:24,446 --> 00:14:25,948
You bastards!

227
00:14:26,031 --> 00:14:28,075
[MACKY GRUNTS]

228
00:14:28,158 --> 00:14:30,536
[EMIL] You're being rude, kid.

229
00:14:30,619 --> 00:14:33,247
Learn to respect your elders!

230
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:37,126
Besides, your father
has only given us cash.

231
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:39,753
There's something else we need.

232
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:41,755
[EMIL SCOFFS]

233
00:14:41,839 --> 00:14:47,928
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

234
00:14:53,350 --> 00:14:54,852
[LUCAS] Senator.

235
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,233
I'll come with you.

236
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:04,403
[SINISTER LAUGH]

237
00:15:06,196 --> 00:15:09,158
[LUCAS] I'm not playing games
with you, Senator.

238
00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:10,868
Don't worry!

239
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:15,748
Are you scared your boat
might get a scratch?

240
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:18,751
You have nothing to worry about.

241
00:15:19,543 --> 00:15:22,379
We know how to drive that boat.

242
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:29,470
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:32,765
[LUCAS CHUCKLES]

244
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:36,101
Just stay here.

245
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:38,437
There's something else you need to do.

246
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:40,147
What?

247
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:48,197
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

248
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:51,784
I'm Lucas Sebastian.

249
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:53,869
Ex-Special Forces.

250
00:15:54,578 --> 00:15:56,080
I have a brother.

251
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,916
He worked as a bouncer.

252
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:01,961
He's currently in prison.

253
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:05,839
Gun smuggling, same case as mine.

254
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:07,549
We were imprisoned together.

255
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:10,761
But I got out earlier.

256
00:16:10,844 --> 00:16:14,056
Because even if I was the mastermind,

257
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:16,934
and my brother only delivered goods,

258
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:19,645
he took the fall for me.

259
00:16:20,437 --> 00:16:25,401
He said that he managed
the operations instead of me.

260
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:28,445
[EDUARDO] Why are you telling me this?

261
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:30,447
What does that have to do with me?

262
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:33,409
You'll do anything for your son.

263
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:38,205
We're the same, Senator.

264
00:16:38,288 --> 00:16:41,375
I'll do anything for my brother.

265
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:47,923
Use your power and influence to free Homer

266
00:16:48,924 --> 00:16:50,634
Sebastian.

267
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:53,846
Your son's life

268
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,682
for my brother's life.

269
00:16:56,765 --> 00:17:01,645
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

270
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:06,650
And don't meddle with
the police officers' plans.

271
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:10,029
That's fine, isn't it?

272
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:15,325
You have an understanding
with Captain Jacinto anyway.

273
00:17:17,619 --> 00:17:19,705
Get back to your work.

274
00:17:20,914 --> 00:17:22,916
Go back to the Senate.

275
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:26,378
Go write some laws.

276
00:17:26,462 --> 00:17:31,925
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

277
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:46,106
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYS]

278
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:49,234
- Cariaso.
- Sir.

279
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:53,947
Update.

280
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:55,657
The pathway is still safe.

281
00:17:57,326 --> 00:17:59,411
We need to start evacuating people.

282
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:01,330
Prepare the hostages.

283
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,957
We'll leave the island
as soon as possible.

284
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:05,334
Copy, sir.

285
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:13,008
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS]

286
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:22,935
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:24,895
Oh, sorry.

288
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:27,397
I'm sure they're busy.

289
00:18:30,734 --> 00:18:32,945
What's happening isn't right.

290
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:34,404
I know.

291
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:36,532
Some VIPs have died already

292
00:18:36,615 --> 00:18:38,909
before we even got the ransoms for them.

293
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:41,662
That's not what I mean.

294
00:18:41,745 --> 00:18:43,497
The plan was so simple.

295
00:18:44,331 --> 00:18:45,791
Take some hostages.

296
00:18:45,874 --> 00:18:47,126
Get their money.

297
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:48,377
Escape.

298
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:51,130
So why did we end up massacring people?

299
00:18:52,047 --> 00:18:55,634
I'm just following Boss Emil's orders.

300
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:58,846
I am the boss.

301
00:18:59,555 --> 00:19:01,849
Do you understand?

302
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:03,100
I'm the boss!

303
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:07,146
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:08,313
Yes, boss.

305
00:19:15,529 --> 00:19:17,906
[MUFFLED GROANS]

306
00:19:20,492 --> 00:19:21,702
[MUMBLES]

307
00:19:23,245 --> 00:19:24,913
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GROANS]

308
00:19:25,914 --> 00:19:27,207
[HISSES]

309
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:29,126
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

310
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:30,627
What did you do?

311
00:19:31,753 --> 00:19:34,923
Sorry, Boss.
We just took out some trash.

312
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:38,635
"Trash"? You've only made a bigger mess!

313
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:41,096
That's a police officer! He's a major!

314
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:43,557
A lot of people will look for him!

315
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:45,976
[LUCAS] He's already received
many death threats from drug lords.

316
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:48,854
Besides, aren't you happy?

317
00:19:48,937 --> 00:19:51,106
Nobody will suspect you anymore.

318
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:52,941
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

319
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:54,902
Less trash.

320
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:57,196
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

321
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:05,787
<i>- Abandoned resort?</i>
<i>- It's not on the map.</i>

322
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:07,623
[EMIL] <i>Give us directions quickly.</i>

323
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:09,208
<i>What do you plan to do with Ian?</i>

324
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,459
[OLSEN] <i>We'll take him with us.</i>

325
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:13,420
[FIN]<i> I'm sorry, but you won't be able</i>
<i>to say goodbye to your friends.</i>

326
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:16,340
- [FIN]<i> He escaped!</i>
- [OLSEN] <i>They can't have gotten far.</i>

327
00:20:16,423 --> 00:20:17,925
[LIAM, OLSEN]<i> Let's go!</i>

328
00:20:19,092 --> 00:20:21,094
<i>- Liam's missing.</i>
<i>- Olsen's gone missing too.</i>

329
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:23,055
<i>Let's surrender already.</i>

330
00:20:23,138 --> 00:20:25,599
<i>- I grew up on this island!</i>
<i>- Brother!</i>

331
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:27,643
[DADO] <i>I'm only taking</i>
<i>back what's ours!</i>

332
00:20:27,726 --> 00:20:30,646
<i>We're heading towards Magnus Roja!</i>

333
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:32,522
<i>We need to leave right now!</i>

334
00:20:32,606 --> 00:20:34,024
[MAGNUS] <i>I will look for them.</i>

335
00:20:34,107 --> 00:20:36,526
[GUNSHOTS]

336
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:39,529
[OLSEN] <i>We need to get ahead of them.</i>

337
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:43,283
<i>I won't leave here</i>
<i>without my husband and son!</i>

338
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:47,537
[EMIL] <i>You're the reason why my other</i>
<i>daughter's life was ruined!</i>

339
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:48,914
[GUNSHOTS]

340
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:51,875
<i>You deceived Ayen!</i>

341
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:54,378
<i>You almost killed my child.</i>

342
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:57,673
<i>You two should die instead.</i>

343
00:20:57,756 --> 00:20:59,466
<i>I'll put an end to this now!</i>
